      "code": "import sys\nimport math\n\ndef solve():\n    N, P = sys.stdin.readline().split()\n    N = int(N)\n    P = float(P)\n    \n    if P == 0.0:\n        print(0)\n        return\n    \n    low = 0\n    high = N\n    answer = N\n    \n    while low <= high:\n        mid = (low + high) // 2\n        # Calculate probability for mid studied maps\n        total = 0.0\n        # Cases where 1, 2, or 3 maps in the selected three are studied\n        # For each case, compute the probability that the remaining map is studied\n        # Total probability is sum over m=1,2,3 of [ C(mid, m) * C(n-mid, 3-m) / C(n,3) * prob_remaining_studied ]\n        \n        # Total combinations C(N,3)\n        c_n3 = math.comb(N, 3)\n        if c_n3 == 0:\n            prob = 0.0\n        else:\n            prob = 0.0\n            # m is the number of studied maps in the selected 3\n            for m in range(1, 4):\n                if m > mid or (3 - m) > (N - mid):\n                    continue\n                c_k_m = math.comb(mid, m)\n                c_nk_3m = math.comb(N - mid, 3 - m)\n                ways = c_k_m * c_nk_3m\n                # Probability that the remaining map is studied: \n                # For m studied maps in 3, the remaining is studied if the other two players discard the other two maps (if m=1), or other cases.\n                if m == 1:\n                    # The studied map is remaining only if both players discard the other two. Each player has 3 choices, total 3*3=9 possible choices.\n                    # Only (2 choices for Johnny) * (1 choice for opponent) = 2 cases where the studied remains.\n                    # Wait, no. For m=1, the three maps are S, U1, U2. Johnny picks one to discard, opponent picks one.\n                    # The remaining is S only if Johnny discards U1 or U2, and opponent discards the other U.\n                    # Johnny has 2 choices (U1 or U2), opponent must pick the remaining U.\n                    # So favorable is 2 * 1 = 2 out of 3*2=6 (since after Johnny picks, opponent picks from remaining two)\n                    # So probability is 2/6 = 1/3.\n                    prob_part = ways * (1.0 / 3)\n                elif m == 2:\n                    # Maps are S1, S2, U. The remaining is studied unless both pick S1 and S2.\n                    # Total 3*2=6 possible choices. Favorable cases:\n                    # Johnny discards S1, opponent discards U \u2192 remaining S2.\n                    # Johnny discards S2, opponent discards U \u2192 remaining S1.\n                    # Johnny discards U, opponent discards S1 \u2192 remaining S2.\n                    # Johnny discards U, opponent discards S2 \u2192 remaining S1.\n                    # So 4 out of 6 cases.\n                    prob_part = ways * (4.0 / 6)\n                elif m == 3:\n                    # All three are studied. Any discards leave a studied map.\n                    prob_part = ways * 1.0\n                else:\n                    prob_part = 0.0\n                prob += prob_part\n            prob /= c_n3\n        if prob >= P - 1e-9:\n            answer = mid\n            high = mid - 1\n        else:\n            low = mid + 1\n    print(answer)\n\nsolve()",
