rable is 2 * 1 = 2 out of 3*2=6 (since after Johnny picks, opponent picks from remaining two)\n                    # So probability is 2/6 = 1/3.\n                    prob_part = ways * (1.0 / 3)\n                elif m == 2:\n                    # Maps are S1, S2, U. The remaining is studied unless both pick S1 and S2.\n                    # Total 3*2=6 possible choices. Favorable cases:\n                    # Johnny discards S1, opponent discards U \u2192 remaining S2.\n                    # Johnny discards S2, opponent discards U \u2192 remaining S1.\n                    # Johnny discards U, opponent discards S1 \u2192 remaining S2.\n                    # Johnny discards U, opponent discards S2 \u2192 remaining S1.\n                    # So 4 out of 6 cases.\n                    prob_part = ways * (4.0 / 6)\n                elif m == 3:\n                    # All three are studied. Any discards leave a studied map.\n                    prob_part = ways * 1.0\n                else:\n                    prob_part = 0.0\n                prob += prob_part\n            prob /= c_n3\n        if prob >= P - 1e-9:\n            answer = mid\n            high = mid - 1\n        else:\n            low = mid + 1\n    print(answer)\n\nsolve()",
